        "type": "mcq",
        "question": "Simplify: $\\frac{\\sec^2 x - 1}{\\sin^2 x}$.",
        "options": [
          "$\\sec^2 x$",
          "$\\csc^2 x$",
          "$\\tan^2 x$",
          "$\\cot^2 x$"
        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$\\sec^2 x - 1 = \\tan^2 x = \\frac{\\sin^2 x}{\\cos^2 x}$, so $\\frac{\\frac{\\sin^2 x}{\\cos^2 x}}{\\sin^2 x} = \\frac{1}{\\cos^2 x} = \\sec^2 x$."
