        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$\\cos(2\\theta) = 2\\cos^2\\theta - 1 = 2\\left(\\frac{15}{17}\\right)^2 - 1 = \\frac{450}{289} - \\frac{289}{289} = \\frac{161}{289}$."
